We must therefore suppose (i) that he did this, or had a lapse of memory, or, (ii) that the words are a scholium coming from some one who was misled by the ambiguity in § 45. The latter appears more probable, since a false statement of this kind would have been easily exposed. Illo ipso die can only mean ‘that same day': cf. Fam. v. 2. 8.
